        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Assistance for Planting Vegetable Crops for Raw and Ripe Mandap&amp;quot; introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to offer financial support to farmers across Gujarat for constructing vegetable trellises (mandaps) using wooden/bamboo supports and GI/plastic wires.\n",
        "benefits_md": "&gt; **Raw Mandap (Tomato/Chilli and other vegetables):**\n\n\n\n    - General Farmers: 50% subsidy, up to ₹26,000/ha.\n    - SC/ST Farmers: 75% subsidy, up to ₹39,000/ha.\n\n\n&gt; **Semi-ripe Mandap (Vine vegetables):**\n\n\n\n    - General Farmers: 50% subsidy, up to ₹40,000/ha.\n    - SC/ST Farmers: 75% subsidy, up to ₹60,000/ha.\n\n\n&gt; **Ripe Mandap (Vine vegetables):**\n\n\n\n    - General Farmers: 50% subsidy, up to ₹80,000/ha.\n    - SC/ST Farmers: 75% subsidy, up to ₹1,20,000/ha.\n\n\n&gt; **Other Support Details:**\n\n\n\n    - Maximum area eligible: 2 hectares per farmer.\n    - Construction material: 1600 wooden/bamboo poles per hectare, 400 kg GI wire (12-18 gauge) or plastic wire.\n    - Recommended spacing: 2.50 x 2.50 meters.\n\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme provides financial assistance to farmers in Gujarat for setting up vegetable trellises (Mandap) for raw, semi-ripe, and ripe vegetables, with varying support for General, SC, and ST farmers.\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
